linkPreview.title: An Unsteady Moment for Tech
linkPreview.description: The past decade has been one long party for tech. Where we go from here isn’t so clear.

linkPreview.title: Inside Twitter, Fears Musk Will Return Platform to Its Early Troubles
linkPreview.description: Content moderators warn that Elon Musk doesn’t appear to understand the issues that he and the company will face if he drops its guardrails around speech.

linkPreview.title: Twitter reports growth in revenue and users as Elon Musk prepares to take over.
linkPreview.description: The social media company reported a 16 percent jump in daily active users from a year ago.

linkPreview.title: Truth Social Review: Trump’s Uncensored Social App Is Incomplete
linkPreview.description: The Trump-backed social media app is inundated with phony accounts and features that don’t work. It also hides some posts, including those with curse words.

linkPreview.title: Snap unveils a flying camera called Pixy.
linkPreview.description: The drone camera is the newest hardware product from the maker of Snapchat, which previously released smart glasses known as Spectacles.

linkPreview.title: Musk’s Ties to China Could Create Headaches for Twitter
linkPreview.description: Elon Musk has invested heavily in China, where officials are willing to influence or punish companies that cross political red lines.

linkPreview.title: Amazon reports slowing sales growth and indicates slowdown may continue.
linkPreview.description: Amazon benefited from the coronavirus pandemic as people flocked to online shopping. Now, shoppers’ behavior has shifted.

linkPreview.title: Apple’s growth slows, but still beats Wall Street’s expectations.
linkPreview.description: While the company did better in its first three months of the year than many of its tech peers, it warned that Covid problems in China will be an issue.

linkPreview.title: Instacart Searches for a Direction as Its Pandemic Boom Fades
linkPreview.description: The grocery delivery start-up changed its leadership, slashed its valuation and shifted its strategy after sales slowed.

linkPreview.title: James Corden Says He’ll Leave His CBS Show Next Year
linkPreview.description: The British-born host, who was a successful actor and comedian before joining the network’s late-night lineup, has been signaling for some time that he was considering leaving.
